   <refnamediv>
       <refname>mcov </refname>
               <refpurpose>White's X'WX </refpurpose>
   </refnamediv>
 
        <refsynopsisdiv>
               <title>CALLING SEQUENCE</title>
               <synopsis>[xuux]=mcov(x,u)</synopsis>
        </refsynopsisdiv>
 
        <refsection>
           <title>PARAMETERS</title>
           <variablelist>
           <varlistentry>
 
           <term>Input</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> x </term> =   nobs x nvar explanatory variables matrix</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>*  <term> u </term> =   nobs x 1 residuals</para></listitem>
 
 
 
<listitem><para>&#160;</para></listitem>
 
           </varlistentry>
 
          <varlistentry>
 
          <term>Output</term>
 
<listitem><para>* <term>xuux</term> such that xpx-inverse*xuux*xpx-inverse represents a heteroscedasticity consistent variance-covariance matrix</para></listitem>
 
 
          </varlistentry>
          </variablelist>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
 Computes x'*u*u'*x.  References: H. White 1980, Econometrica Vol. 48 pp. 818-838.
 
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>EXAMPLE</title>
              <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
xuux = mcov(x,resid);
// Example taken from hwhite. Should not have many other uses.
 
               ]]></programlisting>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>AUTHOR</title>
Eric Dubois 2002
        </refsection>
</refentry>
